From: morikawa <morimoriyuki552@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] fix(gtk): report full cell rect to IM context setCursorLocation

Wayland compositors (e.g. Niri) use the cursor rectangle reported via
text-input-v3 to place the IME candidate popup. When the popup would
overflow below the screen edge, Niri flips it above the anchor rect.

Previously ghostty reported a 1x1 px rect whose origin is the *bottom*
of the cursor cell. On flip, the popup's lower edge aligns with the
cell's bottom, covering the line being typed.

Fix: pass the full cell rectangle (top-left origin + cell dimensions)
so that on upward flip the popup sits above the current line.

---
 src/apprt/gtk/class/surface.zig | 6 +++---
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/apprt/gtk/class/surface.zig b/src/apprt/gtk/class/surface.zig
--- a/src/apprt/gtk/class/surface.zig
+++ b/src/apprt/gtk/class/surface.zig
@@ -1232,9 +1232,9 @@ fn keyPressedSignalGtk(widget: *gtk.Widget, keyval: c.guint, keycode: c.guint,
             if (priv.core_surface) |surface| {
                 const ime_point = surface.imePoint();
                 priv.im_context.as(gtk.IMContext).setCursorLocation(&.{
                     .f_x = @intFromFloat(ime_point.x),
-                    .f_y = @intFromFloat(ime_point.y),
-                    .f_width = 1,
-                    .f_height = 1,
+                    .f_y = @intFromFloat(ime_point.y - ime_point.height),
+                    .f_width = @intFromFloat(@max(1.0, ime_point.width)),
+                    .f_height = @intFromFloat(ime_point.height),
                 });
             }
